{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "eazyvtc-notifications",
    "name": "EazyVTC API — Notifications",
    "description": "# EazyVTC — Module Notifications (Sprint 5)\n\n## Endpoints couverts\n- `POST   /notifications/token`         → Enregistrer le token FCM de l'appareil\n- `DELETE /notifications/token`         → Supprimer le token FCM\n- `GET    /notifications`               → Liste des notifications (paginée + filtres)\n- `PATCH  /notifications/read-all`      → Tout marquer comme lu\n- `PATCH  /notifications/:id/read`      → Marquer une notification comme lue\n- `POST   /notifications/send`          → Envoi manuel (admin/manager uniquement)\n- `POST   /cron/notifications/reminders`→ Rappels 1h avant course (CRON_SECRET)\n\n## Prérequis\n1. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev`\n2. Avoir dans Supabase :\n   - Un compte `client@test.com` (rôle client)\n   - Un compte `driver@test.com` (rôle driver, statut active)\n   - Un compte `admin@test.com` (rôle admin)\n3. Firebase optionnel en local — les notifications sont créées en base même sans FCM configuré\n\n## Ordre d'exécution recommandé\n1. **🔐 Setup — Tokens** : obtenir les 3 tokens + sauvegarder client_user_id\n2. **👨‍💼 Admin — Envoi manuel** : créer une notification de test (sauvegarde notification_id)\n3. **📱 Token FCM** : tester enregistrement / suppression token\n4. **🔔 Lecture des notifications** : tester GET avec filtres et pagination\n5. **✅ Marquer comme lu** : tester markAsRead et markAllAsRead\n6. **⏰ Cron** : déclencher le rappel automatique\n7. **🔒 Contrôle d'accès** : vérifier 401 / 403 / 400 / 404\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `client_token`, `driver_token`, `admin_token`\n- `client_user_id` — pour les requêtes admin (envoi ciblé)\n- `notification_id` — après envoi admin, réutilisé pour markAsRead",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",        "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",     "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_user_id",  "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Sauvegardé depuis Login Client — utilisé pour POST /notifications/send" },
    { "key": "notification_id", "value": "", "type": "string", "description": "Sauvegardé après envoi admin — utilisé pour PATCH /:id/read" },
    { "key": "cron_secret",     "value": "votre-secret-aleatoire-32-caracteres", "type": "string", "description": "Valeur de CRON_SECRET dans .env" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "description": "Exécuter ces 3 requêtes en premier pour remplir client_token, driver_token et admin_token. Le Login Client sauvegarde aussi client_user_id nécessaire pour les envois admin.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "Login Client",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"client@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Client1234!\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('client_token + client_user_id sauvegardés', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', data.access_token);",
                "  if (data.user && data.user.id) {",
                "    pm.collectionVariables.set('client_user_id', data.user.id);",
                "    console.log(' client_user_id:', data.user.id);",
                "  }",
                "  console.log(' client_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Driver1234!\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('driver_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', data.access_token);",
                "  console.log(' driver_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin1234!\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', data.access_token);",
                "  console.log(' admin_token OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "👨‍💼 Admin — Envoi manuel",
      "description": "Envoi manuel d'une notification par un admin vers un utilisateur cible. Nécessite client_user_id (sauvegardé au Login Client). Sauvegarde notification_id pour les tests markAsRead.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[Admin] Envoyer — trip_assigned au client",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/send", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "send"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{client_user_id}}\",\n  \"type\": \"trip_assigned\",\n  \"title\": \"Chauffeur assigné\",\n  \"body\": \"Jean Dupont prendra en charge votre course du 15 juin.\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"reservation_id\": \"00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "pm.test('Notification créée + notification_id sauvegardé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.id).to.be.a('string');",
                "  pm.expect(data.type).to.equal('trip_assigned');",
                "  pm.expect(data.channel).to.equal('push');",
                "  pm.expect(data.status).to.be.oneOf(['pending', 'sent', 'failed']);",
                "  pm.expect(data.title).to.equal('Chauffeur assigné');",
                "  pm.expect(data.body).to.include('Jean Dupont');",
                "  pm.collectionVariables.set('notification_id', data.id);",
                "  console.log(' notification_id sauvegardé:', data.id);",
                "  console.log('   Status FCM:', data.status, '(failed = Firebase non configuré en local — normal)');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Admin] Envoyer — document_validated au driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/send", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "send"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{client_user_id}}\",\n  \"type\": \"document_validated\",\n  \"title\": \"Document validé\",\n  \"body\": \"Votre Permis de conduire a été validé par l'équipe.\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"doc_type\": \"license\"\n  }\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "pm.test('Type document_validated correct', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.type).to.equal('document_validated');",
                "  pm.expect(data.data).to.deep.include({ doc_type: 'license' });",
                "  console.log(' Notification document_validated créée:', data.id);",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Admin] Envoyer — reservation_cancelled",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/send", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "send"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{client_user_id}}\",\n  \"type\": \"reservation_cancelled\",\n  \"title\": \"Réservation annulée\",\n  \"body\": \"Votre course du 15 juin a été annulée par l'équipe. Motif : Indisponibilité chauffeur.\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                "pm.test('reservation_cancelled sans champ data (optionnel)', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data.type).to.equal('reservation_cancelled');",
                "  pm.expect(data.data).to.be.null;",
                "  console.log(' data null quand non fourni — OK');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[400] Envoyer — type invalide",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/send", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "send"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{client_user_id}}\",\n  \"type\": \"type_inexistant\",\n  \"title\": \"Test\",\n  \"body\": \"Corps de test\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 400 — type invalide rejeté par Zod', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                "pm.test('Erreur de validation', () => {",
                "  const { ok, errors } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.false;",
                "  pm.expect(errors).to.have.property('type');",
                "  console.log(' Erreur type:', JSON.stringify(errors.type));",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[400] Envoyer — user_id non-UUID",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/send", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "send"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"pas-un-uuid\",\n  \"type\": \"trip_assigned\",\n  \"title\": \"Test\",\n  \"body\": \"Corps de test\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 400 — user_id non-UUID rejeté', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                "pm.test('Erreur sur user_id', () => {",
                "  const { ok, errors } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.false;",
                "  pm.expect(errors).to.have.property('user_id');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[400] Envoyer — title trop long (> 100 chars)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/send", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "send"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{client_user_id}}\",\n  \"type\": \"trip_assigned\",\n  \"title\": \"AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAA\",\n  \"body\": \"Corps valide\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 400 — title > 100 chars rejeté', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                "pm.test('Erreur sur title', () => {",
                "  const { errors } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(errors).to.have.property('title');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "📱 Token FCM",
      "description": "Gestion du token Firebase Cloud Messaging de l'appareil mobile. Le token est stocké dans la colonne device_token de la table users.",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[Client] Enregistrer token FCM",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/token", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "token"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_token\": \"fGE3j_mKuC8:APA91bHPRgkFjJtmAeRwU5kG7QZk3xVyToken_Test_EazyVTC_Local_Dev\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Token enregistré', () => {",
                "  const { ok, message } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(message).to.include('Token FCM');",
                "  console.log(' Token FCM enregistré en base (colonne device_token sur users)');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Enregistrer token FCM — mise à jour",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/token", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "token"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_token\": \"fGE3j_NOUVEAU:APA91bHPRgkNouveauToken_Apres_Reinstallation_App\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200 — mise à jour idempotente', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Idempotence : même endpoint pour créer ou mettre à jour', () => {",
                "  const { ok } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  console.log(' Remplacement token OK — un seul token par utilisateur');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[400] Enregistrer token trop court (< 10 chars)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/token", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "token"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_token\": \"court\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 400 — token trop court rejeté par Zod', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));",
                "pm.test('Erreur de validation', () => {",
                "  const { ok, errors } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.false;",
                "  pm.expect(errors).to.have.property('device_token');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Supprimer token FCM (déconnexion)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/token", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "token"] }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Token supprimé', () => {",
                "  const { ok, message } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(message).to.include('Token FCM supprimé');",
                "  console.log(' device_token mis à null en base — plus de push pour ce device');",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Re-enregistrer token (après delete)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",  "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }
            ],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications/token", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["notifications", "token"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"device_token\": \"fGE3j_mKuC8:APA91bHPRgkFjJtmAeRwU5kG7QZk3xVyToken_Test_EazyVTC_Local_Dev\"\n}"
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200 — re-enregistrement après suppression', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "const { ok } = pm.response.json();",
                "pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;"
              ]
            }
          }]
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🔔 Lecture des notifications",
      "description": "GET /notifications — Liste paginée avec filtres. Requiert notification_id sauvegardé (depuis envoi admin).",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "[Client] Liste toutes les notifications (défaut)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["notifications"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Structure pagination valide', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  pm.expect(data).to.include.keys(['notifications', 'total', 'unread_count', 'page', 'limit', 'total_pages']);",
                "  pm.expect(data.notifications).to.be.an('array');",
                "  pm.expect(data.page).to.equal(1);",
                "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(20);",
                "  console.log('Total notifications:', data.total, '| Non lues:', data.unread_count);",
                "  if (data.notifications.length > 0) {",
                "    const n = data.notifications[0];",
                "    pm.expect(n).to.include.keys(['id','type','channel','status','title','body','read_at','created_at']);",
                "    if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('notification_id')) {",
                "      pm.collectionVariables.set('notification_id', n.id);",
                "      console.log(' notification_id sauvegardé depuis liste:', n.id);",
                "    }",
                "  }",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Liste — non lues uniquement (unread_only=true)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications?unread_only=true",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["notifications"],
              "query": [{ "key": "unread_only", "value": "true" }]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Toutes les notifications retournées sont non lues', () => {",
                "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
                "  data.notifications.forEach(n => {",
                "    pm.expect(n.read_at).to.be.null;",
                "  });",
                "  console.log('Notifications non lues:', data.total);",
                "});"
              ]
            }
          }]
        },

        {
          "name": "[Client] Liste — page 1, limit 5",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/notifications?page=1&limit=5",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["notifications"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page",  "value": "1" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "5" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": {
              "exec": [
                "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                "pm.test('Pagination respectée', () => {",
                "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
                "  pm.expect(data.page).to.equal(1);",
                "  pm.expect(data.limit).to.equal(5);",
                "  pm.expect(data.notifications.length).to.be.at.most(5);",
                "  pm.expect(data.total_pages).to.equal(Math.ceil(data.total / 5));",
                "  console.log('Page 1/5 résultats — total_pages:', data.total_pages);",
                "});"
